The paper discusses the application of deep learning techniques, specifically Bayesian neural networks, for remaining useful life estimation in condition-based maintenance. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Bayesian neural networks also suggests a focus on uncertainty quantification, which is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the application of these techniques to a popular dataset suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV).
